---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Blind Ant | Charli-Jo Tyrer"
  description="Blind Ant is the conceptual art practice of Charli-Jo Tyrer: a gallery of design-fiction Collections, Pieces and People made using generative AI as an artistic medium."
>
  <h1>Blind Ant</h1>

  <p class="site-intro">
    Blind Ant is the conceptual art practice of Charli-Jo Tyrer, using generative AI as an artistic medium to build design-fiction worlds that readers can inhabit.
  </p>

  <img
    src="/images/blind-ant-logo.png"
    width="1640"
    height="1536"
    alt="A small black ant carrying a bright shard of glass across a dark surface. The fragment reflects light like a signal beacon. The ant appears small but purposeful, suggesting persistence and the quiet movement of ideas."
    loading="eager"
    decoding="async"
  />

  <section aria-labelledby="collections">
    <h2 id="collections">Collections</h2>
    <p>
      Collections are curated exhibitions of Objects drawn from different Pieces and brought together by one curatorial eye.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/collections/burlesque/">Burlesque</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="pieces">
    <h2 id="pieces">Pieces</h2>
    <p>
      Pieces are complete design-fiction worlds composed of one or more Objects.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/pieces/deathbot-2000/">DeathBot 2000</a></li>
      <li><a href="/pieces/do-androids-dream-of-electric-ants/">Do Androids Dream of Electric Ants?</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="people">
    <h2 id="people">People</h2>
    <p>
      People persist across Pieces. They may be people, organisations or institutions that appear throughout the work.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/people/big-charli/">Big Charli</a></li>
      <li><a href="/people/jessica-martinez/">Jessica Martinez</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="about-blind-ant">
    <h2 id="about-blind-ant">About Blind Ant</h2>
    <p>Blind Ant is part of the CharliVerse, the wider body of work created by Charli-Jo Tyrer.</p>
    <p><a href="https://github.com/CharliVerse">CharliVerse on GitHub</a></p>
  </section>
</Base>
